Cooper Companies Inc filed with theSecurities and Exchange Commission for a proposed offering ofup to 300 mln dlrs of senior extendible notes set to mature onJanuary 1, 1993.    Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc will act as an underwriter forthe proposed offering, Cooper said.    Proceeds from the offering will be used to repay debt, forgeneral corporate purposes, and to support future growth. Reuter&#3;